ed Film|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/08/10/disney-gives-marvel-fans-first-look-at-big-hero-6-animated-film|accessdate=9 August 2013|newspaper=IGN|date=9 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"USATodayTruitt\">{{cite web|last=Truitt|first=Brian|title=Meet the saviors of San Fransokyo in 'Big Hero 6'|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/07/13/big-hero-6-character-reveal-exclusive/12535005/|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=July 14, 2014|date=July 13, 2014}}</ref> Wasabi is depicted as a smart, slightly neurotic, heavily built neat-freak and an expert on laser cutting at San Fransokyo Institute of Technology. Also, he stated that Fred gave him his nickname after he spilled wasabi on his shirt one time. On the character, co-director [[Chris Williams (director)|Chris Williams]] said \"He's actually the most conservative, cautious\u2014he [''sic''] the most normal among a group of brazen characters. So he really grounds the movie in the second act and becomes, in a way, the voice of the audience and points out that what they\u2019re doing is crazy.\"<ref name=\"USATodayTruitt\" /><ref name=\"DeadlineMayaJames\">{{cite web|last1=Yamato|first1=Jen|title=Maya Rudolph, James Cromwell, More Join Disney\u2019s Marvel Animation \u2018Big Hero 6\u2032|url=http://deadline.com/2014/07/disney-big-hero-6-voice-cast-804122/|publisher=Deadline|accessdate=September 5, 2014|date=July 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Wasabi|url=https://thismoment-a.akamaihd.net/other/1410708542-2030.pdf|publisher=xprizechallenge.org|accessdate=September 24, 2014}}</ref> This version uses plasma blades generated from the wrists of his suit.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://marvel.wikia.com/Wasabi-No_Ginger_%28Earth-616%29 Wasabi-No-Ginger] at Marvel Wiki\n* [http://www.comicvine.com/wasabi-no-ginger/4005-57495/ Wasabi-No-Ginger] at Comic Vine\n{{Big Hero 6}}\n[[Category:Big Hero 6 characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional swordsmen]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics superhe